PRECIOUS was asleep in her room at ga-Joel Section in Mokomene when the thug gained entry through the window. Police say 21-year-old Precious Ramabulana was attacked by an unknown man and brutally stabbed to death. Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said Precious’ wild screams were heard by the neighbour who called the police. On arrival, her body was found in a pool of blood with several stab wounds.   The Provincial Commissioner of the South African Service in Limpopo Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba has instructed that this brutal killer must be hunted down and brought to book. Ramabulana is from Nzhelele outside Thohoyandou and was a student at Capricorn TVET College, Ramokgopha Campus.  Mojapelo urged anyone with information the brutal incident to call the Police Crime Stop Number 0860010111 or contact the nearest police. 